Sentencas: The stability and surface composition of La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3 - delta (LSCF)-Sm0.2Ce0.8O2 (SDC) cathodes prepared by impregnation are investigated at 750 degrees C under open circuit and different oxygen partial pressures.
Titulo: Effects of oxygen partial pressure on the performance stability of impregnated La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ-Sm0.2Ce0.8O2 cathodes of solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The performance degradation during the test at Po-2 = 0.21 atm is closely related to the low frequency mass transfer process.
Titulo: Effects of oxygen partial pressure on the performance stability of impregnated La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ-Sm0.2Ce0.8O2 cathodes of solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Little change of the electrochemical performance of cathodes is observed after 24 h test at Po-2 = 0.001 atm.
Titulo: Effects of oxygen partial pressure on the performance stability of impregnated La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ-Sm0.2Ce0.8O2 cathodes of solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: XPS patterns show that the decrease in oxygen partial pressure leads to the suppression of Sr enrichment on the surface of cathodes and retards the performance degradation.
Titulo: Effects of oxygen partial pressure on the performance stability of impregnated La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ-Sm0.2Ce0.8O2 cathodes of solid oxide fuel cells
